race.comment: WATERMELON (1) is a course/distance specialist who was quickly back on track scoring by 3.5 lengths as the public elect. Keeps the 3kg claim and she's well-placed to go back-to-back. AUTUNNO (5) placed second behind the above and it was a good effort after an awkward start. He's likely to settle back again but will hit the line. WEEKEND ARTIST (7) found a place over a middle distance at Gatton in Maidens and will carry a feather this grade with a 3kg claim atop. That gives him some hope. BRENTWOOD (2) has been racing well short of his best but tumbles in grade and has the winkers on again. Steps up to this distance for the first time and can run into a minor slot.
